headline: What SoftBank's Sagging Stock Price Says About AI Sentiment
summary: The AI stock frenzy is cooling, and SoftBank is taking it on the chin.  In all, more than $100 billion in market value has been erased.  The roller-coaster ride likely reflects shifting investor sentiment about artificial intelligence, and particularly about ChatGPT maker OpenAI, to which SoftBank has committed more than $31 billion this year.

It applies equally well to what is happening Monday following the launch of  Alphabet  new Gemini 3.  The company, whose stock is by far the best-performing member of the so-called Magnificent Seven so far this year, unveiled the latest version of its chatbot last week.

headline: Don't chase Google's highs; consider other Big Tech AI laggards
summary: Investors are chasing "the flavor of the week" when it comes to the AI trade, Jefferies senior analyst Brent Thill tells Yahoo Finance. Thill highlights Wall Street's enthusiasm with Alphabet (GOOG, GOOGL), while Meta (META) and Oracle (ORCL) fall out of favor. The analyst says the Big Tech stock moves are part of an "over-exaggerated" trade, and suggests that investors buy the dips in Meta and Oracle rather than chasing Alphabet's momentum.
